loreData.archeon.apaflorite.desc: Oh! I found small pink gems on my way! It seems like it's quite durable... Used it to make some equipment... I mean, there are threats everywhere. Not that I'm bad at surviving! Even when there's nothing moving, caves are always dangerous due to the dripstones inside them... Sometimes they're even glowing into the darkness. It's kind of cool... I guess?
loreData.archeon.apaflorite.title: Apaflorite
loreData.archeon.archeology.desc: Wipe here, wipe there... Maybe one day we'll finally discover something interesting hidden in the ground? Seen some menhirs in the water, though they don't seem to be home to any loot. People from villages nearby say that there's nothing interesting anyway. I don't believe that. There must be something hidden underground... Even a simple crypt... Something.
loreData.archeon.archeology.title: Archeology
loreData.archeon.artifacts.desc:
I found some quite very interesting things in here... Sounds like books...

First, from what I've seen, some of them talked about a P...Pick of Kolm? Quolm? Qolm? don't know, but a big magic, and green pickaxe. Second, the Dagger of the Massacre, a powerful weapon making the enemies bleeding just with a simple hit? That sounds pretty basic, huh.

Also, two rings, the Ring of Eden, and the Ring of Wahven. The Ring of Wahven lies at the center of the Panopticon, they say. Wait... who are... 'they'?
loreData.archeon.artifacts.title: Artifacts
loreData.archeon.clementium.desc:
Just found this bright orange metal thingy. I tested melting it and making new tools, and they were incredibly efficient! Although... Seems to be as strong as soaked paper after a simple day of use. I also tested combining it with some exyriane shards, and it felt way more durable, I have to say!

Even after searching everywhere, I couldn't find it anywhere else than into pots or chests... Normally, every metal has an ore, huh? Or maybe it's some kind of alloy. - Back from the village just now. It's indeed an alloy... but nobody seems to know what it's really made of. The way to use it properly is so awkward too, maybe its creation wasn't even wanted. It's called "Clementium".
loreData.archeon.clementium.title: Clementium
loreData.archeon.columns_and_pots.desc:
I was searching for some new things when I found these columns on my way! From the stony and mossy look, they must be... wah, old, oh, and sometimes, you can find some pots on them, pots, urns? I believe it's the same thing! Anyways.

 Columns are small chiaspen buildings, like landmarks? Their sizes are always different... Some just aren't columns but menhirs! Menhirs don't even have something interesting to loot though...
loreData.archeon.columns_and_pots.title: Columns & Menhirs
loreData.archeon.culinary_arts.desc: Something nice about this place is how full of food it is. It's everywhere... And everything seems like it'd taste absurdly good with some of our original world's food. For example... salted heifer steaks! They're so good even though they're basically raw! And mwah, blood oranges too, I think they're called Ihæliámðán around there, litteraly 'little golden fruits'. Also birds are tasty. It feels wrong to say that. Eh.
loreData.archeon.culinary_arts.title: Culinary Arts
loreData.archeon.exyriane.desc: I found beautiful crystals in a small cave on my way! Their blue shimmer is always nice to see. It's called Exyriane. Apparently, they can be used as fuel, but also to make torches! (Which is pretty useful for exploring if you ask me), eh!
loreData.archeon.exyriane.title: Exyriane
loreData.archeon.faelite.desc: Faelite's really a beautiful ore. You can see it far away, when caving. It's of a beautiful purple mixed with orange. It's very durable to use when crafted into equipment... Plus, it's so light to wear. Doesn't look like it, I guess. People say it's not really worth going for mining to find some, since it's pretty common in loot chests. I like doing both... Because both are good ways of exploring what this place has to offer, uh?
loreData.archeon.faelite.title: Faelite
loreData.archeon.fauna.desc: This world has some interesting fauna... Even though it feels like I've discovered like a percent of it... no more. Although I just want to tame one of those birds now! (Yes, I'm talking about the sunstradivers, they're so cute! ...But beware not to let them around snails, they'll just snatch them!)
loreData.archeon.fauna.title: Fauna
loreData.archeon.flora_alchemy.desc: The flower of this continent is just fascinating. Full of colors, full of alchemy. First, it's really nice to decorate your home with those. ...I'll talk about the lycorises first. They're common flowers here, existing in pink, red and orange. Making jam out of their petals is absolutely delicious! Plus, it seems like they can give you special effects depending on the type of petals.
loreData.archeon.flora_alchemy.title: Flora Alchemy (Part 1/2)
loreData.archeon.flora_alchemy_sequel.de: Recently found some flowers named Organdeanes, Iopeas and Oeas... Oeas are like little puffs... Small clouds for a cute interior thingy. Organdeanes can be so tall sometimes, I mean, someone's size approximately, see what I'm talking about? Their purple is really cool to look at though. And last, Iopeas are just simple bushy flowers. Like our world's lilac.
loreData.archeon.fruits.desc: Bah, I'm bored. It's been like a month since I've last found something interesting... And then here I am, building sand castles like a child... Meh, have to say, that sand is way better than our world's. It's so much thicker, it's so easy to do everything you want with it. Also if you're lucky enough, you'll find some of those colorful shells buried into it! It feels cozy here. Warm, and nice...
loreData.archeon.fruits.title: Dune Sunset
loreData.archeon.glass_confections.desc: Said it a while ago... The sand we take from the dunes is just so good at everything... Even when it comes to glass! Making beautiful-shaped windows has never been so easy! Just by putting some curves here and there, it adds some sort of aura to your little home. I have one now, it's cute and cozy, on the sandy shore!
loreData.archeon.glass_confections.title: Glass Confections
loreData.archeon.heart_of_nature.desc: Legends are always the same. Vague or just dumb. But this one, it has something to it... It feels way too real. The context's way too precise. A 'synthesis'-based creature... Some kind of heart holding the power of flora and fauna together, an abomination created by the inhabitants themselves. Or at least, that's what they pretend. They say it's someone in particular. They say it's not attacking alone; they say it's ontop of a black but lush tower.
loreData.archeon.heart_of_nature.title: Heart of Nature
loreData.archeon.lusonyth.desc:
Sometimes, I do trade with the villagers of this continent. They're clam and nice to everyone. They gave me a present, a sort of gemstone, a blue and chunky one, a darker than Exyriane.

They said it's a Lusonyth gemstone, and that it's used a lot for repairing tools made of Clementium, you know, that thing I've talked about earlier. But it can also work as a standalone material! It seems ridiculously good for making tools and armor. Maybe I'll use it... Maybe I'll sell it. Don't know yet anyway.
loreData.archeon.lusonyth.title: Lusonyth
loreData.archeon.seashells.desc: Seashells... Just like at home... I mean, real, real home. Colorful too... They're easily made into tiles, or shingles, whatever you call what you put on your roof to make it a protection against harsh weather. Don't try to make shoes out of seashells. That doesn't work at all.
loreData.archeon.seashells.title: Seashells
loreData.archeon.stones.desc:
Finally, I am starting to write about the stones types of this continent. Found really a bunch of new rocks!

First, Chiaspen, a bright and gray stone which makes up a majority of the place, it's a solid rock, used for architecture like columns, pillars...

There is also Artemnite, a bright beige rock I found. It is not that different from home's limestone. It's also kinda cool to carve them into bricks, or ornate them with a bit of Exyriane making it look so cool! Pretty sure you can also do that with that dark stone they call Aketite!
loreData.archeon.stones.title: Stones (Part 1/2)
loreData.archeon.stones_sequel.desc: Criadan's a beautiful stone, really. It's of a soothing beige that can be easily carved into bricks, pillars and more... It's just nice to look at when you don't want something too harsh for decoration. Also inhabitants of the continent are apparently known for engraving star-shaped symbols into them, like they do with another stone; Phosnor. But there's not much to say about it aside from the fact that it's found very deep underground.
loreData.archeon.stones_sequel.title: Stones (Part 2/2)
Just want to tame one, already said it! They're so cute! Sunstradivers are just little birds that beg to be carressed! They don't seem to fear any species anyway, and we're not exception to that. Also, they eat, and by that, I mean, a lot! Snails in majority.
loreData.archeon.the_panopticon.desc: A prison, they say. Lost to time, simply 'lost' they said. They don't really understand how marvelous it'd be to discover such a building. An arena, a jail? Or maybe both? It sounds dreamy and terrifying at the same time. That's probably why I want to explore it... I want to find it. I need to see.
loreData.archeon.the_panopticon.title: The Panopticon
loreData.archeon.the_tower_of_atmosphere: That same legend I've talked about earlier... it mentions the Heart's home, an immense tower, reaching up to the skies. You'd need a key for accessing its reward... Apparently. It was referred as one of the most beautifuls works of architecture in Septentrionea. I mean, the land with two capitals; 'Lillí-Thœdáhn' and 'Lillí-Liám'.
loreData.archeon.wood.desc: There are trees everywhere, so wood really isn't a problem here. It's so abundant! Can make tools out of their wood, although they're terribly clunky. Meh, who cares anyway, since now I have this shiny equipment. Building wood-based structures' still always a fun thing though.
loreData.archeon.wood.title: Wood
